  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Cervical radiculopathy defined by neck pain irradiating to one arm with at least one
             of the following: provocation by neck movements or sensory changes in one or more
             adjacent dermatomes or diminished deep tendon reflexes in the affected arm; or muscle
             weakness in one or more adjacent myotomes.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Arm pain existing longer than one month

          -  Clinical signs of spinal cord compression

          -  Previously treated with physiotherapy or a cervical collar
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
